01:30:26,207 --> 01:30:33,954
<i>This was perhaps the first decent
thing they ever did for Matilda.</i>

688
01:30:34,132 --> 01:30:37,750
And here.

689
01:30:40,013 --> 01:30:43,964
Come here. Turn around.

690
01:30:45,935 --> 01:30:52,389
- You won't want support payments?
- No. We have everything we need.

691
01:30:52,568 --> 01:30:56,233
Let's roll.

692
01:31:09,877 --> 01:31:14,125
<i>So Harry and Zinnia got away.
And as bad as things were, -</i>

693
01:31:14,299 --> 01:31:18,428
<i>- that's how good they became.</i>

694
01:31:20,222 --> 01:31:26,806
<i>Miss Honey was made
principal of the school.</i>

695
01:31:26,979 --> 01:31:32,733
<i>And Matilda found, to her surprise,
that life could be fun.</i>

696
01:31:32,902 --> 01:31:36,520
<i>She decided to have
as much fun as possible.</i>

697
01:31:36,698 --> 01:31:40,529
<i>After all, she was a very smart kid.</i>

698
01:31:55,092 --> 01:32:02,222
<i>Matilda and Miss Honey each got
what they had always wanted:</i>

699
01:32:02,391 --> 01:32:06,223
<i>A loving family.</i>

700
01:32:06,395 --> 01:32:11,188
<i>And Matilda never had to use
her powers again.</i>

701
01:32:11,359 --> 01:32:14,775
<i>Well. I mean almost never.</i>

702
01:32:24,164 --> 01:32:26,833
"Call me Ishmael."

703
01:32:27,000 --> 01:32:33,132
"Some years ago,
never mind how long, precisely..."

